	<h3>Throwback: FOAF Vocabulary Specification</h3><a href="http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/">FOAF Vocabulary Specification</a>.&nbsp; [originally posted 2004-05-06-1042 -0700] This is apparently the specification for Friend-Of-A-Friend (FOAF).&nbsp; I found the Foaf-a-matic and created a little FOAF file for myself.&nbsp; I'm not sure what that proves.&nbsp; I edited it a little bit but it doesn't give me much to go by.&nbsp; This specification is immersed in RDF and OWL and Semantic Web technology, and all I want to know is just what is this.&nbsp; I also have trouble decoding the copyright claim.&nbsp; I think I will steer clear until I'm satisfied there's no volcano in all the magma.<br>
